  <description type="morphology">Aerial stems  lasting less than a year, occasionally overwintering in the southwestern United States, usually unbranched, 20--150 cm; lines of stomates single; ridges 10--32.  Sheaths  green, elongate, 7--15 × 3--9 mm; teeth 10--32, articulate and usually shed early, leaving dark rim on sheath.  Cone  apex rounded to apiculate with blunt tip; spores green, spheric. 2 n =216.</description>
